        <mxCell id="0sATpbcnCbdbjLfDtfcH-45" parent="1" style="whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=0;" value="Original Regression Y = B&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;X;+ error. If the correlation/covariance between one of the original variables X and error, there is endogeneity bias.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;Identify instruments Z that affect X but not Y, regress X onto Z, obtain estimates for X, X* (+ controls)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Then regress Y onto X* (+ controls).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="130" width="200" x="1000" y="770" as="geometry" />
